## Third-Party Components

This software incorporates code and concepts from the following sources:

### GPS Receiver Communication
Based on original implementations by:
- Fjalar Sigurdsson (fjalar@vedur.is), Veðurstofan Íslands
- FTP communication protocols for Septentrio PolaRX5 receivers
- GPS data download and archiving workflows

### Dependencies  
- GTimes library for GPS time processing
- Rich library for enhanced console output
- ProgressBar2 for download progress tracking

### Scientific Standards
Receiver communication follows:
- GNSS receiver manufacturer specifications
- FTP/SFTP protocols for data transfer
- RINEX format standards for GPS data
- IGS station monitoring guidelines

## Attribution

If you use Receivers in operational or scientific applications, please consider citing:

```
Ófeigsson, B. G., & Sigurdsson, F. (2024). Receivers: GPS/GNSS receiver 
management and data download toolkit. Veðurstofan Íslands (Icelandic Met Office).
https://github.com/vedur-is/receivers
```

## Disclaimer

This software is provided for operational and scientific purposes. While every
effort has been made to ensure reliability, users should validate functionality
for their specific receiver configurations and network environments. 

The authors and Veðurstofan Íslands assume no responsibility for any consequences 
arising from the use of this software, including but not limited to data loss or 
receiver malfunction.

For critical operational applications, users should maintain appropriate backup
procedures and monitoring systems.